ABUJA (Sundiata Post) Amina Zakari, a national commissioner at the Independent and National Electoral Commission (INEC), has been appointed to head the collation centre of the 2019 elections. In the wake of the news, unconfirmed reports have emerged that she is President Buhari’s niece, and this doesn’t sit well with alot of Nigerians on social media. See tweets:       Zakari was appointed to head the committee on collation centre, one of the two committees for the election which the commission inaugurated on Thursday in Abuja. Speaking during the inauguration, Mahmood Yakubu, INEC chairman, said the committee shall be responsible for the national collation centre – the International Conference Centre – from where results of the Presidential election will be announced.